{"TopicId":149215,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"77I - Lowell Gandini","CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T18:57:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T18:57:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Trebuchet MS\u0027, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E77 Racing - Lowell Gandini 1975\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221rwIn5p.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/1rwIn5p.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are two car designers who\u0027s work I love the most: Robert Opron, famous for the Citro\u00EBn DS type 3, the Citro\u00EBn GS, the Citr\u00F6en CX and the Citro\u00EBn SM. The other is Marcello Gandini, famous for the Lamborghini Countach, Miura and Espada, the Alfa Romeo Carabo, the Maserati Khamsin and the Citro\u00EBn BX, the car I own and drive since 2003. Obviously, my favourite period in car design is the 1970\u0027s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PmCgzuA.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/PmCgzuA.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis fictional \u0022Italian\u0022 \u0022supercar\u0022 is a homage to Gandini. It uses elements of multiple of his designs, most prominently the wedge, the louvres above the engine and the Kamm tail. It\u0027s powered by fuel cells and 3 Juno\u0027s. As a first it uses a \u0022boost flap\u0022 to cut thrust from the jet engines, this works much faster than using the throttle considering the\u003Cstrong\u003E unrealistic \u003C/strong\u003Espool times of the jet engines in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry guys, no pop-up headlights on this one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bhtrMs8.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/bhtrMs8.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s fun to drive!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpecs:\u003Cbr\u003E\nParts: 148.\u003Cbr\u003E\nLxWxH: 6.4 x 2.4 x 1.7.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMass tanks full: 8899 kg.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMass tanks empty: 7999 kg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerformance:\u003Cbr\u003E\nAcceleration: 0-100 km/h: 4 seconds (using both electric and turbines).\u003Cbr\u003E\nTop speed: 267 km/h.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMax sustained speed in a turn: 238 km/h.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FASE0Ew.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/FASE0Ew.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload link:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalx.com/crafts/18637\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://kerbalx.com/crafts/18637\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot compatible with KSP 1.1.3 or older!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-04T00:24:23Z\u0022 title=\u002210/04/2016 12:24  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 4, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Azimech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T22:05:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far as I\u0027m aware\u00A0you can instantly cut thrust to a jet by action grouping the intake. It\u0027s a trick I picked up from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/62843-cupcake/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002262843\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/62843-cupcake/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cupcake...\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0years ago. :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-03T22:08:19Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2016 10:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-03T22:23:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222785959\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149215\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475532348\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far as I\u0027m aware\u00A0you can instantly cut thrust to a jet by action grouping the intake. It\u0027s a trick I picked up from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/62843-cupcake/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002262843\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/62843-cupcake/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cupcake...\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0years ago. :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting ... that would indeed work even faster\u00A0 :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder If I can use it with the brake action group though ... think I\u0027ll use both. Thanks for the tip!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: closing the intakes instantly cuts thrust, yes. Unfortunately they have to spool up again after opening, which is slow. I\u0027ll keep the flap as main toggle, it\u0027s good for racing ... no \u0022turbo lag\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-03T22:30:55Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2016 10:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Azimech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-04T00:24:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload is ready, updated \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}